is
necessary
to
roughly
calculate
the
square
inch
area
of
the
opening
but
the
calculation
can
usually
be
made
with
sufficient
accuracy
that
it
won't
affect
the
final
computation
.

Compute
this
volume
by
measuring
the
distance
from
the
top
of
the
block
to
the
piston
head
as
accurately
as
possible
with
a
depth
micrometer
or
some
other
precision
