Discovery
of
electromagnetism

In
the
late
1700's
Beccaria
and
Van
Marum
,
among
others
,
had
magnetized
iron
by
sending
an
electrostatic
charge
through
it
.

Beccaria
had
almost
stumbled
on
a
lead
to
the
relationship
between
electricity
and
magnetism
when
a
discharge
from
a
Leyden
jar
was
sent
transversally
through
a
piece
of
watch-spring
steel
making
its
ends
magnetic
.

The
resulting
magnetic
effect
proved
stronger
than
when
the
discharge
was
made
lengthwise
.

The
sequence
of
events
leading
to
his
important
discovery
still
