obtained
and
other
allied
matters
.

Whereas
the
maintenance
rotary
fund
had
in
the
past
sustained
losses
considerably
beyond
expectations
,
the
introduction
of
the
cost-billing
system
plus
other
control
refinements
has
resulted
in
keeping
the
fund
on
a
proper
working
basis
.

In
order
to
further
refine
the
management
of
passenger
vehicles
,
on
July
1
,
1958
,
the
actual
