after
two
years
,
rather
than
44,000
miles
(
and
related
higher
maintenance
costs
)
and
16,000
miles
respectively
''
.

The
motor
pool
is
a
completely
centralized
and
mechanized
operation
.

It
handles
all
types
of
vehicle
maintenance
,
but
concentrates
more
on
``
service
station
activities
''
than
on
extensive
vehicle
repairs
.

It
contracts
with
outside
repair
garages
for
much
of
the
latter
work
.

One
matter
of
concern
to
the
complete
effectiveness
of
pool
operations
is
the
lack
of
adequate
central
garage
facilities
.

Purchasing
practices
.

The
