Poland

When
the
Yalta
Conference
opened
,
the
American
policy
of
postponing
all
discussion
of
Russia's
western
boundaries
until
the
peace
conference
had
broken
down
.

Starting
in
great
force
late
in
December
,
from
a
line
stretching
from
East
Prussia
to
Budapest
,
the
Red
armies
had
swept
two
hundred
miles
across
Poland
to
the
Oder
,
thirty
miles
from
Berlin
,
and
the
Upper
Danube
region
was
being
rapidly
overrun
,
while
the
Western
Allies
had
not
yet
occupied
all
of
the
left
bank
of
the
Rhine
.

He
stood
up
to
emphasize
his
strong
feeling
on
the
subject
.

The
West
had
long
since
forgotten
the
events
of
1919
,
but
it
was
not
so
easy
for
the
Red
leaders
,
who
felt
that
they
had
suffered
great
