of
the
Germans
.

The
issue
was
left
in
abeyance
,
presumably
for
the
peace
conference
.

Believing
devoutly
as
they
did
in
Anglo-Saxon
institutions
,
it
was
important
to
both
Roosevelt
and
Churchill
that
the
Poles
should
have
them
.

More
time
was
