.

Microorganisms
are
often
responsible
for
the
rapid
spoilage
of
foods
.

Enzymatic
action
in
stored
food
produces
changes
which
can
adversely
affect
the
appearance
of
food
or
its
palatability
.

Spoilage
by
chemical
action
results
from
the
reaction
of
one
group
of
components
in
the
food
with
others
or
with
its
environment
,
as
in
corrosion
of
the
walls
of
metal
containers
or
the
reaction
of
fats
with
oxygen
in
the
air
to
produce
rancidity
.

General
effects
of
ionizing
radiation

Because
of
undesirable
